  "texts": [
    "These attributes are further reflected in the RCA network's high classification accuracy of 99% in Table 2, underscoring its capability to perform well on datasets where scenes exhibit high feature consistency and separation.",
    "Table 2 presents the outcomes of our proposed methodology in comparison with four cutting-edge approaches for remote sensing image scene classification using the PatternNet dataset.",
    "As evident in Table 2, our proposed method achieves an impressive overall classification accuracy of 99% on the PatternNet test dataset.",
    "This result is notably superior, surpassing the accuracy of multitask learning network (MTLN), error-tolerant deep learning (ETDL), Extracting Hierarchical and Collaborative intertarget feature Alignment (EHACA), and VGG-16 by 7%, 4%, 4%, and 2%, respectively.",
    "The effectiveness of our approach is further substantiated in Fig. 9, illustrating its commendable accuracy, reaching 97% accuracy across 38 categories, with most categories achieving over 98% accuracy.In contrast, the framework exhibited diminished performance for the EuroSAT dataset in accurately identifying the herbaceous vegetation class."
